            "Modern families. Talk about your family. Tell one fun or interesting story about your family or childhood.": "Modern families come in many forms: single-parent, blended, adoptive or multigenerational. My own family is small — my parents, my younger sister, and me. We support each other in studies and hobbies. A fun story: once my dad wanted to cook a special dinner but he mixed up salt with sugar by mistake. We ended up eating sweet meat! We laughed a lot and ordered pizza instead. That evening taught me that mistakes can turn into warm memories. Family is not about perfection, it's about love and laughing together. I believe that sharing small funny moments builds strong relationships.",
            "Speak about the Seven natural wonders of America.": "America has breathtaking natural wonders: Grand Canyon, Yellowstone, Yosemite, Niagara Falls, Redwood Forest, Great Smoky Mountains, and Death Valley. The Grand Canyon shows colourful rock layers carved by the Colorado River over millions of years. Yellowstone has amazing geysers like Old Faithful and hot springs. Niagara Falls produces massive water power and mist. The Redwood trees in California are among the tallest living things. These wonders remind us to protect nature. Visiting them makes you feel small and amazed. I dream to see the giant sequoias — some are thousands of years old. Nature's beauty connects people across cultures.",
            "Speak about climate extremes.": "Climate extremes include heatwaves, floods, droughts, hurricanes, tornadoes and blizzards. For instance, heatwaves in Europe cause wildfires and health problems. Heavy monsoons in Asia flood villages and destroy crops. In the Arctic, temperatures are rising faster than elsewhere, causing ice melting. These extremes affect farming, water supply, and human health. People adapt by building stronger houses and using early warning systems. Global cooperation is needed to reduce carbon emissions. In my country, winters are freezing and summers are hot. Climate change makes weather more unpredictable. We should all take small steps — save energy, plant trees — to protect our planet.",
            "Speak about Britain's colonial past.": "Britain had a huge empire that once covered nearly a quarter of the world. Colonies included India, Canada, Australia, and many African countries. While the empire spread English language, railways, and legal systems, it also caused exploitation, slavery, and cultural damage. After World War II, independence movements grew strongly. Today the Commonwealth connects former colonies in a voluntary partnership. Britain's colonial past left complex legacies — from curry becoming a national dish in Britain to debates about statues of colonial figures. Understanding this history helps us talk about immigration, multiculturalism and inequality in modern Britain.",
            "Speak about the history at the movies.": "Historical movies like 'Braveheart', 'The King's Speech', '1917' and 'Gladiator' bring past events to life on screen. They make us feel emotions, see costumes, battles and great speeches. However, movies often change facts for drama. For example, 'Gladiator' mixes real and fictional characters. Still, films inspire interest in history. After watching 'Schindler's List', many people learned about the Holocaust. I love 'The Imitation Game' about Alan Turing. Movies can start conversations about what really happened and why it matters today. They make history accessible, especially for young people.",
            "the USA making the news in the 20th century.": "The 20th century USA saw many headline events: World Wars, the Great Depression, the Civil Rights Movement, the moon landing, and the Cold War. In the 1960s, Martin Luther King Jr. fought for racial equality. The Vietnam War caused huge protests across the country. Technology boomed with computers, space exploration and the internet. The 9/11 attacks happened in 2001, changing global security forever. American news shaped global opinion – from jazz and Hollywood to politics. Learning about these events helps understand modern America's power, challenges, and cultural influence worldwide.",
            "UK parliament: tradition...": "The UK Parliament is one of the oldest in the world, based in Westminster, London. Traditions include the State Opening, where the Queen or King reads a speech prepared by the government. The 'Black Rod' is sent to summon the Commons and the door is shut in his face — symbolising independence. The Speaker of the House of Commons wears a wig and robe. MPs debate laws, and the House of Lords reviews them. These traditions show respect for history, but parliament also modernises — now you can watch debates online or on TV. I find it curious that 'division bells' ring to call MPs to vote. Tradition keeps democracy connected to heritage.",
            "The ups and downs of the British monarchy": "The British monarchy has survived for over a thousand years. Ups: uniting the nation, royal ceremonies like weddings, and tourism. The Queen Elizabeth II was a symbol of stability for 70 years. Downs: scandals like King Edward VIII's abdication, and criticism about costs. Some people love the royals; others want an elected head of state. Today King Charles III faces debates about relevance and modernisation. However, the monarchy adapts — for instance, the Crown Estate gives profits to the government. Personally, I respect tradition but think transparency is important.",
            "Extreme sports": "Extreme sports include rock climbing, skydiving, surfing big waves, base jumping and snowboarding. People enjoy adrenaline, pushing limits and feeling free. Safety is crucial – training and good equipment save lives. Famous places: New Zealand for bungee jumping, Hawaii for big-wave surfing, the Alps for skiing. Extreme sports teach focus, courage and respect for nature. However, they can be dangerous, so participants need experience and preparation. I would like to try paragliding to see mountains from above. These sports also create strong communities. The Olympics now includes skateboarding and climbing, showing how extreme sports become mainstream.",
            "Street dancing": "Street dancing started in the 1970s in New York City, including breaking, popping and locking. It comes from hip-hop culture and block parties. Dancers express themselves with rhythm, acrobatics and freestyle. Famous crews like the Rock Steady Crew made it popular worldwide. Today street dance is in music videos, competitions like 'World of Dance' and even the Olympics. It's inclusive – anyone can join regardless of age or background. I love the energy and creativity. Street dance breaks barriers and builds confidence. My favourite style is popping because of the robotic and fluid moves.",
            "Star pupils.": "Star pupils are students who excel academically or in extracurricular activities. They are curious, hardworking, and help others. Being a star pupil isn't only about grades – it's about attitude and kindness. For example, a student who organises charity events shows leadership. Schools celebrate star pupils to motivate peers. In my class, a friend is great at math and also teaches younger kids for free. I admire discipline, curiosity and generosity. Anyone can become a star pupil by setting goals, staying organised, and supporting classmates. Success is a journey, not just awards.",
            "Languages in Canada and Wales.": "Canada has two official languages: English and French, especially in Quebec. Wales also has two official languages: English and Welsh. In Wales, road signs are bilingual, and children learn Welsh in school. These policies protect minority languages from dying out. About 20% of Welsh people speak Welsh, while in Canada many learn French as a second language. Language preservation is important for cultural identity. I find it inspiring that Wales revived Welsh through education, media and official status. Similarly, Canada supports French culture and immersion programmes. Multilingualism enriches society and keeps ancient traditions alive.",
            "Hollywood kids": "Hollywood kids are child actors who grow up in the film industry. Some, like Drew Barrymore or Jaden Smith, became famous very early. Benefits: money, fame, travel, and creative opportunities. Challenges: pressure to look perfect, balancing school with work, and public scrutiny. Some struggle with addiction or mental health as adults. Others succeed by having supportive families and good managers. Hollywood kids can inspire young talents but also show the dark side of early fame. I think child actors need legal protections, proper education and time to be children. Their stories remind us that childhood should be protected.",
            "Young Masters": "Young Masters refers to talented teenagers or children in art, music, chess, or science. For example, Mozart composed at age five. Today, kids like Akiane Kramarik paint incredible portraits. Social media helps them share work globally. Young masters often practise many hours a day. They need support from families and teachers. Being a prodigy brings recognition but also high expectations. I believe we should celebrate young achievements without burning them out. Many young masters become lifelong creators. Their passion teaches us that age is not a barrier to greatness. Hard work and talent together create miracles.",
            "Movie soundtracks": "Movie soundtracks enhance emotions – from John Williams' 'Star Wars' to Hans Zimmer's 'Interstellar'. A good soundtrack makes you cry, laugh, or feel fear. The 'Titanic' song 'My Heart Will Go On' became iconic worldwide. Soundtracks help storytelling without words. Some movies like 'Guardians of the Galaxy' use old pop songs perfectly. Composers work closely with directors to capture the mood. I often listen to soundtracks while studying or driving. They transport me into the film world. The best soundtracks become classics and stay with audiences long after the credits roll.",
            "US law: show business... and big business": "US law affects show business through contracts, copyright, and labour rules. Big business like streaming platforms (Netflix, Disney, Amazon) negotiate with actors, writers and musicians. The recent writers' strike showed how residuals and AI use are big issues. Intellectual property law protects songs, scripts, and trademarks. In Hollywood, unions like SAG-AFTRA fight for fair pay and safe working conditions. Antitrust laws prevent monopolies in media. For artists, knowing law basics is essential. Business and creativity often clash, but good laws ensure creators earn a living. The entertainment industry is a major part of the US economy.",
            "Hothouse flowers": "'Hothouse flowers' refers to people or things that need special care to thrive. In education, it might mean gifted programs or very protected children. Literally, hothouses (greenhouses) grow delicate plants. Figuratively, some children raised in very protected environments struggle with real-world challenges. However, proper nurturing can help talents bloom. I think everyone needs some support and encouragement. 'Hothouse' can also describe an intense creative scene or a competitive school. Finding balance between protection and resilience is important. We all can grow stronger with the right conditions and a bit of challenge.",
            "High school culture.": "High school culture includes cliques, sports events, proms, academic pressure and social media. In many countries, high school shapes identity and friendships. Extracurriculars like drama, debate or band help students find passions. Popularity, fashion, and social media influence teens a lot. Positive school culture includes anti-bullying campaigns, mental health support, and inclusion. In American films, high school looks dramatic, but real life is more diverse. I think respect and kindness make high school better. Sharing lockers, group projects, and lunch breaks create lasting memories. High school prepares us not only for exams but for life."
        };
        if (longSpeeches[topic]) return longSpeeches[topic];
        return `This topic "${topic}" is important for intercultural communication. You can discuss key points, give examples from your experience, and use vocabulary from the word list. Remember to speak clearly and express your opinion. Good luck!`;
    }

    // ---------------------------- ОТОБРАЖЕНИЕ БИЛЕТОВ ----------------------------
    function renderTickets(filter = "") {
        const grid = document.getElementById("ticketsGrid");
        const f = filter.toLowerCase();
        let visible = 0;
        let html = "";
        tickets.forEach(t => {
            const matchId = t.id.toString().includes(f);
            const matchWord = t.words.some(w => w.toLowerCase().includes(f));
            const matchTopic = t.topic.toLowerCase().includes(f);
            const show = f === "" || matchId || matchWord || matchTopic;
            if (show) visible++;
            if (!show) return;
            html += `
                <div class="ticket-card" data-id="${t.id}">
                    <div class="ticket-header">
                        <span class="ticket-num">🎫 Билет №${t.id}</span>
                        <span class="topic-badge">🗣 Тақырып</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="ticket-preview">
                        <div class="word-cloud">
                            ${t.words.map(w => `<span class="word-chip">📘 ${w}</span>`).join('')}
                        </div>
                        <div class="topic-preview">💬 ${t.topic.length > 85 ? t.topic.substring(0,85)+"…" : t.topic}</div>
                        <div class="click-hint">👆 Толық мағына + дайын жауап ашу</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            `;
        });
        grid.innerHTML = html;
        document.getElementById("ticketCounter").innerHTML = `${visible} / ${tickets.length} билет көрсетілуде`;
        document.querySelectorAll(".ticket-card").forEach(card => {
            const id = parseInt(card.getAttribute("data-id"));
            const ticket = tickets.find(t => t.id === id);
            card.addEventListener("click", () => {
                document.getElementById("modalTicketNum").innerHTML = `🎫 Билет №${ticket.id}`;
                let wordsDefHtml = `<div class="modal-words-section"><h3 style="margin-bottom:16px;">📖 Сөздер және анықтамалары</h3>`;
                ticket.words.forEach(w => {
                    wordsDefHtml += `<div class="word-def-block"><div class="word-term">${w}</div><div class="word-def">💡 ${getDef(w)}</div></div>`;
                });
                wordsDefHtml += `</div>`;
                const speakingText = getSpeakingAnswer(ticket.topic);
                const speakHtml = `<div class="modal-speaking"><strong>🗣 ${ticket.topic}</strong><div class="speak-full" style="margin-top:14px;">${speakingText}</div></div>`;
                document.getElementById("modalBody").innerHTML = wordsDefHtml + speakHtml;
                document.getElementById("modalOverlay").classList.add("active");
            });
        });
    }

    // ---------------------------- ТЕСТ (все уникальные слова) ----------------------------
    let allWords = [];
    const wordSetAll = new Set();
    tickets.forEach(t => t.words.forEach(w => wordSetAll.add(w)));
    allWords = Array.from(wordSetAll);
    let quizQuestions = [], quizIndex = 0, quizAnswers = [], selectedTemp = null;
    function buildQuiz() {
        let qs = [];
        for (let w of allWords) {
            const correct = getDef(w);
            let others = allWords.filter(w2 => w2 !== w).map(w2 => getDef(w2));
            others = [...new Set(others)];
            while (others.length < 3) others.push("a general definition related to culture");
            let opts = [correct, ...others.slice(0,3)];
            for (let i=opts.length-1;i>0;i--) {let j=Math.floor(Math.random()*(i+1));[opts[i],opts[j]]=[opts[j],opts[i]];}
            qs.push({word:w, correct:correct, options:opts});
        }
        for (let i=qs.length-1;i>0;i--) {let j=Math.floor(Math.random()*(i+1));[qs[i],qs[j]]=[qs[j],qs[i]];}
        return qs.slice(0, Math.min(qs.length, 160));
    }
    function renderQuiz() {
        const container = document.getElementById("quizContainer");
        if (quizIndex >= quizQuestions.length) {
            container.innerHTML = `<div style="padding:40px; text-align:center;">🎉 Тест аяқталды! Керемет. Қайта бастау үшін түймені басыңыз.</div>`;
            document.getElementById("nextQuizBtn").style.display = "none";
            return;
        }
        document.getElementById("nextQuizBtn").style.display = "flex";
        const q = quizQuestions[quizIndex];
        const answered = quizAnswers[quizIndex];
        let optsHtml = "";
        const letters = ["A","B","C","D"];
        q.options.forEach((opt,idx) => {
            let style = "";
            if (answered === 1 && opt === q.correct) style = "background:#dff0e4; border:2px solid #2b8c5e;";
            else if (answered === -1 && opt === q.correct) style = "background:#c8f0dc;";
            else if (answered === -1 && selectedTemp === opt && opt !== q.correct) style = "background:#ffe0e0;";
            optsHtml += `<div class="opt" data-opt="${opt.replace(/"/g, '&quot;')}" style="${style}"><span class="opt-letter">${letters[idx]}</span><span>${opt}</span></div>`;
        });
        let feedback = "";
        if (answered === 1) feedback = `<div class="feedback-correct">✅ Дұрыс! «${q.word}» — ${q.correct}</div>`;
        if (answered === -1) feedback = `<div class="feedback-wrong">❌ Қате. Дұрыс жауап: ${q.correct}</div>`;
        container.innerHTML = `<div class="quiz-box"><div class="question-word">📌 ${q.word}</div><div class="options-list" id="quizOptions">${optsHtml}</div>${feedback}<div style="margin-top:16px; text-align:center;">${quizIndex+1} / ${quizQuestions.length}</div></div>`;
        if (answered === 0) {
            document.querySelectorAll("#quizOptions .opt").forEach(el => {
                el.addEventListener("click", (e) => {
                    const chosen = el.getAttribute("data-opt");
                    selectedTemp = chosen;
                    if (chosen === q.correct) quizAnswers[quizIndex] = 1;
                    else quizAnswers[quizIndex] = -1;
                    updateScore();
                    renderQuiz();
                });
            });
        }
    }
    function updateScore() { let cor = quizAnswers.filter(v=>v===1).length; document.getElementById("quizScore").innerHTML = `🏆 Ұпай: ${cor} / ${quizQuestions.length}`; }
    function nextQuiz() { if (quizIndex+1 < quizQuestions.length) { quizIndex++; renderQuiz(); } else if (quizIndex+1 === quizQuestions.length) { quizIndex++; renderQuiz(); } }
    function resetQuiz() { quizQuestions = buildQuiz(); quizIndex = 0; quizAnswers = new Array(quizQuestions.length).fill(0); selectedTemp = null; updateScore(); renderQuiz(); document.getElementById("nextQuizBtn").style.display = "flex"; }

    document.getElementById("searchInput").addEventListener("input", (e) => renderTickets(e.target.value));
    document.getElementById("modalCloseBtn").addEventListener("click", () => document.getElementById("modalOverlay").classList.remove("active"));
    document.getElementById("modalOverlay").addEventListener("click", (e) => { if(e.target === document.getElementById("modalOverlay")) document.getElementById("modalOverlay").classList.remove("active"); });
    document.getElementById("nextQuizBtn").addEventListener("click", nextQuiz);
    document.getElementById("resetQuizBtn").addEventListener("click", resetQuiz);
    renderTickets("");
    resetQuiz();
</script>
